The paper discusses user perceptions of privacy risks associated with smart home IoT devices, which involves aspects of cybersecurity (cs.CR), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and system and control theory (cs.SY). The study also explores user behaviors and preferences related to privacy, which could fall under the categories of social and information networks (cs.SI) and computers and society (cs.CY).
